ews%2Findian-student-who-went-missing-last-month-found-dead-in-london-river-4624389%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Findian-student-who-went-missing-last-month-found-dead-in-london-river-4624389%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BNo%20One%20Thought%20I'd%20Survive%26quot%3B%3A%20When%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20Cheated%20Death%20In%20Burma%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20life%20of%20Field%20Marshal%20Sam%20Hormuzji%20Framji%20Jamshedji%20Manekshaw%20has%20been%20turned%20into%20a%20motion%20picture%2C%20'Sam%20Bahadur%2C'%20which%20was%20released%20today.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20remember%20him%20as%20the%20man%20who%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20bringing%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20to%20its%20knees%20in%201971%2C%20a%20war%20that%20catapulted%20him%20as%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20commanders%20in%20modern%20India%2C%20but%20almost%2030%20years%20ago%20in%201942%20in%20Burma%20(now%20Myanmar)%2C%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20defeated%20death%20to%20become%20a%20war%20hero.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAction%20In%20Burma%2C%201942%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES.H.F.J%20Manekshaw%20was%20posted%20in%20the%204th%20Battalion%20of%20the%2012th%20Frontier%20Force%20as%20a%20Captain%20in%20Burma%20and%20witnessed%20action%20during%20World%20War%20II%20when%20the%20Japanese%20were%20at%20the%20eastern%20doorstep%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Americans%20wanted%20to%20keep%20the%20Japanese%20busy%20in%20China%2C%20while%20the%20Japanese%20Imperial%20Army%2C%20apart%20from%20Burma's%20resources%2C%20wanted%20to%20use%20it%20to%20cut%20off%20American%20military%20supply%20lines%20to%20already%20isolated%20China%20and%20use%20Burma%20as%20a%20launching%20pad%20for%20operations%20in%20British%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESam%20Manekshaw's%204%2F12%20FF%20under%20the%2017th%20Indian%20Infantry%20Division%20was%20deployed%20in%20the%20defense%20of%20Burma%20in%201942.%20The%20stretched%20British%20forces%20retreated%20to%20the%20Sittang%20railway%20bridge%20after%20the%20Japanese%20entered%20Burma%20and%20reached%20the%20Bilin%20River%20almost%2048%20km%20south%20of%20Sittang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20was%20to%20cross%20the%20Sittang%20River%2C%20which%20runs%20north%20to%20south%2C%20and%20a%20small%20bridgehead%20was%20defended%20by%20undermanned%203%20Burma%20Rifles.%20Sam%20Manekshaw's%204%2F12%20FF%20was%20sent%20to%20reinforce%20the%20troops%20on%20the%20east%20of%20the%20bridgehead.%20The%20troops%20had%20to%20cross%20the%20river%20east%20to%20west%20on%20February%2022%20and%20then%20demolish%20the%20bridge%20with%20explosives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAttack%20and%20Counter%20Attack%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESam%20Manekshaw%20was%20commanding%20the%20'A'%20company%20of%204%2F12%20FF.%20The%20soldiers%20from%20the%20Japanese%201%2F215%20Regiment%20emerged%20from%20the%20jungles%20and%20attacked%20the%20Sittang%20village%20to%20take%20over%20the%20bridge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20Battle%20of%20Sittang%20Bridge%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20Battle%20of%20Sittang%20Bridge%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fm2dr2vu8_sittang-bridge-_625x300_01_December_23.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20Battle%20of%20Sittang%20Bridge%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Image%20posted%20on%20Facebook%20by%20Gurkha%20Museum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Japanese%20had%20taken%20control%20of%20the%20Buddha%20and%20Pagoda%20hill%20to%20dominate%20the%20approach.%20Captain%20Sam%20Maneskshaw's%20'A'%20company%20along%20with%20Duke%20Of%20Wellington's%202nd%20Company%20counterattacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECaptain%20Manekshaw%20was%20tasked%20to%20defend%20the%20approach%20from%20the%20left%20of%20the%20Sittang%20bridge.%20The%20counterattack%20was%20successful%2C%20but%20he%20suffered%20nine%20bullet%20injuries%20in%20his%20abdomen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%2C%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20recalls%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20chap%20(Japanese%20soldier)%20emerged%20from%20the%20bushes%20and%20opened%20a%20burst%20of%20fire%20with%20his%20Tommy%20gun.%20I%20received%20nine%20bullets%20in%20my%20abdomen%2C%20and%20no%20one%20thought%20I%20would%20ever%20live.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajor%20General%20David%20Cowan%2C%20the%20GOC-in-C%20of%20the%2017th%20Infantry%20Indian%20Division%2C%20saw%20Captain%20Manekhsaw%20and%20pinned%20his%20Military%20Cross%20on%20the%20injured%20Manekshaw's%20uniform%20to%20honour%20him%20as%20the%20gallantry%20medal%20was%20not%20awarded%20posthumously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Manekshaw%20was%20awarded%20the%20Military%20Cross.%20Clipping%20of%20London%20Gazette%2C%201941%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Sam%20Manekshaw%20was%20awarded%20the%20Military%20Cross.%20Clipping%20of%20London%20Gazette%2C%201941%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F1ejftde_london-gazette-1941_625x300_01_December_23.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESam%20Manekshaw%20was%20awarded%20the%20Military%20Cross.%20Clipping%20of%20London%20Gazette%2C%201942%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHumor%20In%20The%20Face%20Of%20Death%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECaptain%20Sam's%20batman%20(a%20soldier%20assisting%20an%20officer)%2C%20Sher%20Singh%2C%20carried%20him%20on%20his%20shoulder%20to%20the%20surgeon.%20The%20Australian%20doctor%20refused%20to%20treat%20him%20due%20to%20his%20serious%20abdomen%20injuries%20and%20his%20grim%20chances%20of%20survival%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BCan't%20waste%20my%20time%20over%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20regained%20consciousness%