g%20with%20every%20hearing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fkremlin-critic-alexei-navalny-says-he-has-been-handed-new-criminal-charges%2Farticleshow%2F105652339.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fkremlin-critic-alexei-navalny-says-he-has-been-handed-new-criminal-charges%2Famp_articleshow%2F105652339.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fkremlin-critic-alexei-navalny-says-he-has-been-handed-new-criminal-charges%2Famp_articleshow%2F105652339.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Sam%20Bahadur%E2%80%99%3A%20Yet%20Another%20Biopic%20That%20Is%20in%20Awe%20of%20Its%20Protagonist%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01140026%2FScreenshot-2023-12-01-at-1.59.20%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDirector%20Meghna%20Gulzar%20is%2C%20without%20doubt%2C%20someone%20with%20good%20taste.%20Even%20in%20her%20relatively%20minor%20works%2C%20Gulzar%20appears%20earnest%2C%20curious%20and%20shows%20remarkable%20empathy%20for%20her%20characters%20%E2%80%93%20barely%20the%20norm%20in%20mainstream%20films.%20Like%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fraazi-alia-bhatt-review%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERaazi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3E(2018)%2C%20she%20made%20%5Bwhat%20felt%20like%5D%20a%20radical%20choice%20to%20paint%20Pakistani%20soldiers%20as%20mere%20cogs%2C%20rather%20than%20blood-thirsty%20savages%20who%20start%20their%20day%20by%20praying%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHindustan%20ki%20barbaadi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(India%E2%80%99s%20destruction).%20The%20stereotypical%20portrait%20of%20Pakistanis%20was%20something%20most%20of%20Gulzar%E2%80%99s%20colleagues%20were%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20indulge%20in%20at%20the%20time%2C%20given%20how%20it%20proved%20more%20lucrative.%20And%20yet%2C%20the%20Alia%20Bhatt-starrer%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20success%2C%20showcasing%20a%20rare%20instance%20of%20Gulzar%E2%80%99s%20sincerity%20being%20rewarded%2C%20also%20anchoring%20it%20as%20a%20foundational%20value%20in%20her%20films.%20Hence%2C%20what%20is%20most%20baffling%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20the%20many%20adjectives%20it%20throws%20at%20its%20protagonist%20%E2%80%93%20making%20them%20feel%20empty%20and%20some%20of%20the%20key%20storytelling%20choices%20feeling%20reverse-engineered.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%20the%20scene%2C%20when%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20(Vicky%20Kaushal)%20is%20being%20wheeled%20in%20for%20an%20operation%20after%20being%20shot%20several%20times%20by%20a%20Japanese%20soldier.%20A%20British%20doctor%20looks%20at%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20body.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20happened%20to%20you%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asks%2C%20only%20to%20get%20a%20swift%20response%2C%20%E2%80%9CGot%20kicked%20by%20a%20mule.%E2%80%9D%20The%20doctor%20laughs%20and%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnyone%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20humour%20is%20worth%20saving.%E2%80%9D%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20perfectly%20fine%20anecdote%2C%20but%20the%20scene%20feels%20awkwardly%20performed%20between%20the%20two.%20In%20the%20first%20scene%20of%20the%20film%2C%20the%20parents%20of%20a%20baby%20with%20gleaming%20eyes%20(Manekshaw)%20are%20trying%20to%20debate%20what%20they%20should%20name%20him.%20Cyrus%20or%20something%20else%3F%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20mind%20reading%20this%20anecdote%2C%20but%20again%20in%20the%20visual%20medium%2C%20the%20scene%20feels%20too%20staged.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20screenplay%20(co-written%20by%20Meghna%20Gulzar%2C%20Shantanu%20Srivastava%20and%20Bhavani%20Iyer)%20seems%20satisfied%20in%20piecing%20together%20stray%20vignettes%20to%20tell%20a%20birth-to-death%20life%20story%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20Field%20Marshal%20%E2%80%93%20Sam%20Manekshaw%2C%20the%20connective%20tissue%20between%20the%20vignettes%20feeling%20perfunctory%20at%20best.%20It%20might%20not%20be%20entirely%20Gulzar%E2%80%99s%20fault%20though%2C%20given%20how%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20war%20film%20has%20changed%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20and%20the%20ever-increasing%20paranoia%20around%20biopics%20that%20are%20scared%20to%20do%20little%20else%20than%20praise%20their%20subjects.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20most%20Bollywood%20biopics%20should%20be%20titled%20%E2%80%9C%5Binsert%20name%5D%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20hits%E2%80%9D%3B%20so%20cursory%20is%20the%20intent%20to%20investigate%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20complex%20legacy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F6xJptj7AVSA%3Fsi%3DwwcA1ENJEKPh5e_r%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBarring%20Vicky%20Kaushal%2C%20who%20brings%20a%20bravura%20physicality%20to%20the%20titular%20part%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20biopic%20so%20reverential%20in%20its%20treatment%20that%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20even%20dare%20fiddle%20with%20the%20chronology%20of%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20rise%20in%20the%20army.%20The%20film%20begins%20with%20his%20days%20as%20a%20Gentleman%20Cadet%20at%20the%20Indian%20Military%20Academy%20(IMA)%20in%20Dehradun%2C%20his%20meet-cute%20with%20wife%20Silloo%20(Sanya%20Malhotra)%2C%20his%20years%20spent%20in%20the%20British%20Indian%20army%20in%20the%20early%201940s%2C%20his%20proximity%20to%20Yahya%20Khan%20(Mohd%20Zeeshan%20Ayyub)%20%E2%80%93%20who%20goes%20on%20to%20become%20a%20future%20adversary%20during%20the%201971%20Indo-Pak%20war%20%E2%80%93%20and%20then%20concludes%20with%20his%20becoming%20the%20first%20Field%20Marshal%20of%20the%20Indian%20army%2C%20a%20mere%20two%20weeks%20before%20his%20retirement%20in%201973.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20painfully%20%E2%80%98safe%E2%80%99%20film%20that%20is%20in%20much%20awe%20of%20its%20protagonist%2C%20to%20the%20point%20that%20it%20reaffirms%20the%20impact%20of%20his%20every%20monologue%2C%20by%20cutting%20to%20the%20faces%20of%20those%20listening%20to%20him%20with%20their%20jaws%20on%20the%20floor.%20This%20includes%20officers%20investigating%20Manekshaw%20in%20an%20internal%20inquiry%2C%20propped%20up%20by%20a%20jealous%20superior%2C%20where%20he%E2%80%99s%20tried%20as%20an%20%E2%80%98anti-national%E2%80%99.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20like%20she%E2%80%99s%20telling%20the%20audience%20how%20to%20feel%20%E2%80%93%20a%20surprising%20choice%20by%20a%20filmmaker%20of%20Gulzar%E2%80%99s%20calibre.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKaushal%2C%20whose%20last%20blockbuster%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fmovie-review-uri-predictably-patriotic%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EUri%3A%20The%20Surgical%20Strike%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2019)%20coincidentally%20also%20saw%20him%20play%20an%20army%20officer%20on%20screen%2C%20mimics%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20stooped%20posture%20and%20employs%20his%20precise%20manner%20of%20speaking.%20As%20archival%20footage%20seems%20to%20suggest%2C%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20words%20sounded%20like%20a%20machine%20gun.%20There%20were%20few%20pauses%2C%20he%20rarely%20stuttered%20in%20interviews%2C%20and%20there%20seemed%20to%20be%20an%20other-worldly%20conviction%20in%20the%20way%20he%20conducted%20himself.%20Kaushal%20does%20a%20splendid%20job%20of%20birthing%20a%20character%20that%20skirts%20the%20lines%20of%20a%20real-life%20impression%20and%20a%2050s%20%E2%80%98hero%E2%80%99%20with%20go-for-broke%20swagger.%20However%2C%20like%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EUri%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Kaushal%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20is%20never%20reciprocated%20by%20Gulzar%E2%80%99s%20film.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGulzar%20hints%20at%20the%20hurt%20of%20partition%20with%20a%20spectacular%20line%20delivered%20by%20Ayyub%E2%80%99s%20Yahya%20Khan%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20British%20offered%20us%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekhichdi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20then%20gave%20us%20the%20choice%20to%20separate%20the%20rice%20and%20lentils%20for%20ourselves.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20portrayal%20of%20the%20secondary%20characters%20is%20fairly%20one-note%3A%20Nehru%20(Neeraj%20Kabi)%20is%20shown%20as%20a%20leader%20with%20failing%20health%2C%20supple%20wrists%20and%20a%20defeatist%20attitude%20(a%20portrait%20the%20current%20govt%20could%20get%20behind)%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20(Fatima%20Sana%20Sheikh)%20as%20a%20stoic%20stateswoman%20%E2%80%93%20aggressive%20compared%20to%20her%20father%2C%20and%20a%20worthy%20adversary%20to%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20surefire%20way%20of%20operating.%20Ayyub%E2%80%99s%20Yahya%20Khan%20is%20buried%20under%20layers%20of%20prosthetic%20make-up%2C%20but%20his%20arc%20from%20a%20sentimental%2C%20whiskey-loving%20army%20man%20to%20an%20orchestrator%20of%20cold-blooded%20genocide%20is%20only%20dealt%20with%20in%20bullet%20points.%20Sanya%20Malhotra%2C%20playing%20Silloo%20%E2%80%93%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20supportive%2C%20exasperated%20wife%20%E2%80%93%20gets%20even%20less%20to%20do%20here%20than%20she%20did%20earlier%20this%20year%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fwith-jawan-shah-rukh-khan-crosses-over-to-the-south-his-natural-charm-fully-intact%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJawan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20credit%20to%20the%20radiance%20of%20actors%20like%20Sheikh%20and%20Malhotra%20that%20such%20%E2%80%98nothing%E2%80%99%20parts%20even%20register.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20film%20never%20asks%20the%20most%20rudimentary%20questions%20of%20a%20man%20with%20a%20larger-than-life%20stature%3A%20did%20Sam%20Manekshaw%2C%20the%20most%20self-assured%20man%20(as%20suggested%20in%20the%20film)%20ever%20doubt%20himself%3F%20Was%20he%20ever%20tongue-tied%20by%20something%20he%20witnessed%3F%20What%20prompted%20his%20love%20for%20the%20army%20%E2%80%93%20was%20it%20just%20the%20discipline%3F%20What%20does%20a%20filmmaker%20like%20Gulzar%20think%20of%20the%20machismo%20championed%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20Manekshaw%20%E2%80%93%20he%20once%20sent%20bangles%20to%20a%20regiment%20that%20chose%20self-preservation%2C%20over%20possible%20martyrdom%3F%20The%20film%20touches%20upon%20him%20as%20a%20benevolent%20general%2C%20who%20explicitly%20ordered%20his%20soldiers%20to%20treat%20other%20soldiers%20and%20women%20with%20respect%2C%20how%20he%20was%20an%20early%20advocate%20for%20a%20dignified%20pension%20scheme%20for%20members%20of%20the%20armed%20forces.%20They%20feel%20like%20trivia%2C%20without%20necessarily%20taking%20us%20inside%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20head.%20Where%20did%20he%20get%20his%20conviction%20from%3F%20Was%20it%20just%20instinct%20or%20did%20he%20see%20things%20differently%3F%20What%20prompted%20his%20radical%2C%20fearless%20way%20of%20thinking%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20when%20being%20conservative%20and%20thrifty%20was%20being%20inculcated%20to%20the%20nation%20at%20large%3F%20Was%20it%20his%20upper-class%2C%20convent-educated%20upbringing%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20tragedy%20is%20seeing%20Meghna%20Gulzar%20trying%20to%20salvage%20a%20decent%20film%20amidst%20circumstances%20significantly%20out%20of%20her%20control.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20zoom%20out%20for%20a%20bit%3A%20she%E2%80%99s%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20%E2%80%98hit%E2%80%99%20film%20on%20the%20army%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20armed%20forces%20have%20become%20a%20handy%20plaything%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20politicians.%20So%2C%20even%20though%20she%E2%80%99s%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20film%20about%20good%2C%20old-fashioned%20patriotism%20%E2%80%93%20something%20that%20probably%20existed%20during%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20time%20%E2%80%93%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20the%20film%20seems%20like%20it%E2%80%99s%20trying%20to%20appeal%20to%20the%20audience%20who%20lapped%20up%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EUri%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(both%20films%20produced%20by%20Ronnie%20Screwvala%E2%80%99s%20RSVP).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGulzar%E2%80%99s%20studied%2C%20compassionate%20ways%20are%20at%20odds%20with%20a%20market%20that%20demands%20New%20India%E2%80%99s%20brashness%20and%20chest-thumping.%20The%20Shankar-Ehsaan-Loy%20songs%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBadhte%20Chalo%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERabb%20Ka%20Bandah%20Hai%20Yeh%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20both%20of%20which%20appear%20in%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20last%20hour%2C%20feel%20force-fitted%20in%20a%20film%20that%20has%20suddenly%20realised%20that%20it%20also%20needs%20to%20serve%20as%20military%20propaganda.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20neither%20here%2C%20nor%20there.%20I%20wonder%20if%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20would%E2%80%99ve%20approved%20of%20such%20half-measures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701421235000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01140026%2FScreenshot-2023-12-01-at-1.59.20%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fsam-bahadur-biopic-review-meghan-gulzar-vicky-kaushal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Meghna%20Gulzar%E2%80%99s%20film%20never%20really%20gets%20into%20Field%20Marshal%20Manekshaw%E2%80%99s%20mind%2C%20preferring%20to%20just%20record%20the%20key%20moments%20in